  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nEverytime someone requests the head of the chain, 4 32 bytes string have to be converted from string to bytes.\r\n\r\nWhen running a beacon node with many validators (512) 0.8% (400 ms / 45000 ms) of total CPU was spent in `toBlockSummary`. It's not a lot but seems like it a lot of wastefull computations since the head doesn't change that often.\r\n\r\n**Proposed solution**\r\n\r\nCould we store the head both as strings and bytes and expose the already parsed object?\r\n\r\n",
